Title: Whirlpool — At the Heart of Home
Author: wavelet-director

INT. KITCHEN - MORNING

A cream-and-oak kitchen washed in low morning light. On a butcher-block counter, the iconic stand mixer — red enamel cast body, polished steel bowl — sits center frame. The lens drifts slowly toward it. Flour dusts the wood. A wooden spoon rests beside the bowl.

CUT TO:

INT. KITCHEN - MORNING (MACRO)

Inside the bowl. The dough hook turns at low speed, folding a shaggy mass into a smooth elastic dough. Soft steam wisps from a kettle just out of frame. Light catches the curl of dough as it folds.

CUT TO:

INT. KITCHEN - MORNING (PULL BACK)

Two hands cradle the polished bowl and lift it free of the mixer. The stand mixer remains on the counter, still, gleaming, ready for the next bake. Light warms the red enamel.

FADE OUT.
